<docs>
	<doc for="IsVolatile">
		<summary>
			<para>Marks a field as volatile.</para>
		</summary>
		<remarks>
			<para><see langword="IsVolatile"/> is used only in custom modifiers of method signatures to indicate
 that the field it marks is volatile. Any compiler that imports
 metadata with one or more fields marked as volatile must use instructions prefixed with "volatile."
 to access such fields.</para>
			<para>The classes in System.Runtime.CompilerServices are for compiler writers use
 only.</para>
		</remarks>
	</doc></docs>
